The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, August 19, 2004 				 TCS shares to be listed on Aug 25
																								Mumbai, Aug. 18 (PTI): The Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) stock will list on August 25 even as the firm plans to get its shares traded on overseas bourses.																								The listing is slated for August 25, on the Bombay and National stock exchanges, chief executive officer S. Ramadorai, re-designated as managing director of the software major, said here today.																								TCS maiden offer closed on August 5. The issue price for shares with a face-value of Re 1 was fixed at Rs 850.																								Company sources said the expansion of the board, in which several eminent individuals from business would be brought in, would take place at a later date. The board now consists of three directors  Tata group chairman Ratan Tata, eminent banker Aman Mehta and managing director Ramadorai.																								Tata has said in the past that he would set in motion plans to get TCS shares listed on overseas exchanges. However, he did not say how and when he would go about achieving the long-cherished objective.
